Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of machine learning, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks, for the classification of supernovae. This falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with time series data, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
